<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Skakala stream at the northern slopes of Durmitor massif, type locality of Hydraena dinarica, sp. n." , "Figure 6. Hydraena dinarica, sp. n. aedeagus (holotype): A) dorsal view: B) lateral view; scale bar = 0.1 mm." , "Figure 4. Digital habitus photographs of Hydraena dinarica, sp. n., paratype ♂; scale bar = 1.0 mm." , "Figure 5. Hydraena dinarica, sp. n., paratypes: A) ♂ ventral view; B) ♂ elytral apices; C) ♀ elytral apices; D) ♀ ventral abdomen; E) ♀ tergite X; F) gonocoxite; G) ♂ mesotibia; H) ♀ mesotibia; I) ♂ metatibia; J) ♀ metatibia." , "Figure 7. Statistical parsimony haplotype network of successfully sequenced samples of Hydraena dinarica sp. n., H. biltoni, H. minutissima, H. morio, H. nigrita, H. subintegra, two unidentified female specimens and GenBank records of related species from aligned COI sequences of 567 bp length." , "Figure 8. Map of Europe with the collection site of Hydraena dinarica sp. n. and the distribution of morphologically similar species of the \" Haenydra \" lineage defined as \" Hydraena emarginata complex \" by Trizzino et al. (2013 a) and H. gracilis as genetically similar species with overlapping range." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/423880" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/434648" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/423906" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/423864" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/423907" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/433354" .

